{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17476150","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17476150"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:41:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:41:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13587"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13587","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13587"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.55,0.19,0.06,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6198"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67238"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6198","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6198"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13587"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52690"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"42"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"359"},{"type":"tags","id":"1127"},{"type":"tags","id":"1265"},{"type":"tags","id":"2602"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"11676"},{"type":"tags","id":"13217"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"11453"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11535"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16154"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20495"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20726"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42895"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44155"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67238","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67238"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 16-year-old girl presents to her General Practitioner after experiencing an episode of fainting while climbing stairs at school. She reports that just before she fainted, she felt dizzy and had palpitations. She had a similar episode two weeks ago during an exam, which was quite stressful. She exercises regularly and has no significant medical history. Her father died suddenly at age 38, which was suspected to be due to a cardiac event. On examination, she appears well with a blood pressure of 120/75 mmHg, pulse of 72/min in sinus rhythm, and respiratory rate 16/min. Cardiac examination reveals a loud systolic ejection murmur at the left sternal edge that intensifies when she stands from a squatting position. A left ventricular heave is present.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Urgent cardiac MRI","Beta-blocker and urgent echocardiogram","Implantable cardioverter-defibrillator referral","Exercise stress test","24-hour Holter monitor"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features highly suggestive of hypertrophic obstructive cardiomyopathy (HOCM), including exertional syncope, family history of sudden cardiac death, and dynamic murmur. \u003Cstrong\u003EBeta-blocker and urgent echocardiogram\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate initial step as it addresses both immediate symptom control and diagnostic confirmation. Beta-blockers reduce outflow obstruction and decrease risk of arrhythmia, while echocardiography can assess left ventricular wall thickness and outflow tract gradient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUrgent cardiac MRI\u003C/strong\u003E is an important investigation but should follow initial echocardiographic confirmation of the diagnosis. MRI provides detailed assessment of myocardial scarring and helps with risk stratification for sudden cardiac death.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplantable cardioverter-defibrillator referral\u003C/strong\u003E may ultimately be indicated given the high-risk features (family history of sudden death, syncope), but this decision requires comprehensive evaluation including imaging and risk stratification first.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExercise stress testing\u003C/strong\u003E can be dangerous in undiagnosed HOCM and should only be performed after initial evaluation and treatment have been established.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E24-hour Holter monitoring\u003C/strong\u003E is part of the comprehensive evaluation for risk stratification but is not the priority in initial management when compared to establishing the diagnosis and initiating beta-blockade.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe European Society of Cardiology Risk Calculator is used to guide ICD decisions after full evaluation. This includes assessment of wall thickness, left atrial size, family history, unexplained syncope, non-sustained ventricular tachycardia, and abnormal blood pressure response to exercise.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Beta-blockers plus urgent echocardiography are the initial steps in managing suspected hypertrophic obstructive cardiomyopathy.","Family history of sudden cardiac death and syncope are high-risk features requiring urgent evaluation for ICD placement.","Cardiac MRI helps evaluate myocardial scarring and assists with sudden cardiac death risk prediction in HOCM."],"references":["Ommen SR, Semsarian C. Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy: a practical approach to guideline directed management. The Lancet. 2021 Dec 4;398(10316):2102-8.                                                                                                          https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(21)01205-8"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52690"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13587"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52690","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52690"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T09:45:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T09:48:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6198"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67238"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"42","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/42"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddec","name":"Genetics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-2